Every time you travel and move to a new place, you leave a Doppelganger at the old place, the incomplete abandoned old "you", existing as a fossilized ghost, the way your hometown friends remember you, even if it no longer resembles the new living you. A sort of sclerotic demon.
The incentive to seize a woman is greater if you get to pick only one, it's the same logic as Eric Bugenhagen exercising only one lift for weeks at a time every day

You move out of your hometown to go to college. A demon is left static, the you-before-you-left. You live at the new college town, but eventually leave and go back home, leaving a second demon there, the new "old you". Eventually the two demons will meet and destruct each other.
But before that, if you return home and see your demonic Doppelganger living there, you have to face him on your own and get him to leave the house.

Dr. Julius Evola saw fossils of prehistoric archaic "hominids" as the "abortions of a primordial impulse", reflected in myths about the struggle of divine races against monstrous animal-like demons (representing intrinsic animalistic potentialities) before mankind's advent.

These latent animal potentialities were isolated and left behind - extinct "early human races" represent man swept away by them. This fits with "thunderstone" stone tools being seen as weapons, which during the "war in heaven" had been used in driving forth Satan and his hosts.
